text: Kabato District in Sorachi Subprefecture is a district located in Sorachi Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of 2004, the district has an estimated population of 14,944 and a density of 19.99 persons per km². The total area is 747.75 km². ==Towns and villages== *Shintotsukawa *Tsukigata *Urausu Category:Districts in Hokkaido
